Testing #20793

Repro steps:
1. Launch debugging w/ app.js below
```
console.log('hello');
var a = function () {
    return "hi";
}

setInterval(function() {
    console.log(a());console.log(1);
}, 1000);
```
2. Step through until column pointer is as shown below:
![screenshot from 2017-02-22 19-04-13](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/762848/23238827/dca08b20-f931-11e6-8626-3dfd8288f65c.png)

3. Try deleting and re-adding the semicolon, or adding text before the pointer. 
![screenshot from 2017-02-22 19-00-32](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/762848/23238714/492f61ae-f931-11e6-8a89-d9cf90a36e4c.png)

Testing #20793

Repro steps:
1. Launch `app.js` below w/ debugger (Node v.0.12.6, Linux)
```js
setInterval(function() {
    console.log("hello");
}, 1000);
```
2. Hit the breakpoint the first time (everything looks okay)
3. Hit the breakpoint the second time, column pointer appears:
![screenshot from 2017-02-22 18-47-44](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/762848/23238369/a0f977aa-f92f-11e6-9656-81ae8f81b16d.png)
